race.comment: TWISTED STEEL (6) comes here off a 63-day freshen after a disappointing run in the Placid Ark. His form prior was very good, particularly over this trip first-up in the Max Simmonds. Looks a nice horse on the rise and while he's drawn out, he may just be too good for this lot. NICCIMOTA (5) was sound first-up after settling a touch further back and ending up 0.7L off the winner. She'll be fitter for that effort and has the speed to roll across from out wide. Can find the front and be hard to run down with that run under her belt. JUSTABITTAPRESS (8) finished 0.5L off the winner last start at Bunbury when the race favourite. He was off a very long break there and should be better for that performance. Won't be far away. RISE TO GLORY (12) finished off strongly last start over this track and trip and can be in the finish again. EARTH GOD (4) trialled well coming in and can be thereabouts.
